ui-label: Mole Fraction Of Acetaldehyde In Air
description: Mole fraction is used in the construction "mole_fraction_of_X_in_Y", where X is a material constituent of Y. A chemical species denoted by X may be described by a single term such as "nitrogen" or a phrase such as "nox_expressed_as_nitrogen". The chemical formula for acetaldehyde is CH3CHO. The IUPAC name for acetaldehyde is ethanal.
